Iavan pijoos, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Cape Town &ndash; A woman and&nbsp;her&nbsp;son&nbsp;were shot dead&nbsp;and her&nbsp;two other&nbsp;boys&nbsp;were wounded during shooting incidents in Brackenfell, Western Cape on Saturday.It later emerged the two shooting&nbsp;incidents were related and that a mother and her 21-year-old son were fatally shot.The mother's 14-year-old twins were wounded.Earlier ER24 spokesperson &nbsp;Russel Meiring said when paramedics arrived at the first scene they found a mother and her son, both with gunshot wounds.&nbsp;They were declared dead on the scene.The twin brothers were shot at a house in Ultra Road, Brackenfell.&nbsp;Upon their arrival, paramedics found a boy, 14, in the living room with a gunshot wound to his head, Meiring said. &nbsp;He was in a critical condition.&nbsp;His twin brother was found in one of the bedrooms with a gunshot wound to his hand and armParamedics treated the patients and provided the critically injured child with advanced life support interventions.They were transported to Tygerberg Hospital.&nbsp;The details surrounding the incident are not known.&nbsp;Local authorities are investigating.&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.